1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Health – General
4 19–213.
5 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
6 (2) “Facilities” means hospitals and related institutions whose rates have
7 been approved by the Commission.
8 (b) The Commission shall assess and collect user fees on facilities as defined in
9 this section.
10 (c) (1) The total fees assessed by the Commission may not exceed the greater
11 of:
12 (i) 0.1% of the immediately preceding fiscal year’s budgeted,
13 regulated, gross hospital revenue; or
14 (ii) The largest amount determined under this paragraph for a fiscal
15 year during the immediately preceding 5 fiscal years.
16 (2) The total user fees assessed by the Commission may not exceed the
17 Special Fund appropriation for the Commission by more than 20%.
18 (3) The user fees assessed by the Commission shall be used exclusively to
19 cover the actual documented direct costs of fulfilling the statutory and regulatory duties of
20 the Commission in accordance with the provisions of this subtitle and any administrative
21 costs for services to the Commission provided by the Department.
22 (4) The Commission shall pay all funds collected from fees assessed in
23 accordance with this section into the Health Services Cost Review Commission Fund.
24 (5) The user fees assessed by the Commission may be expended only for
25 purposes authorized by the provisions of this subtitle.
26 (6) The amount specified in paragraph (1) of this subsection limits only the
27 total user fees the Commission may assess in a fiscal year.
